cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CC 

This paper is primarily focused on information retrieval (IR) and the interactions between query reformulation and document relevance estimation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also uses game theory to model the interactions between the two aspects of IR, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses practical algorithms for achieving equilibrium in retrieval, which could place it under cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
